Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.98,0:06:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A combination of the two, that faith balances the dedication to truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.17,0:06:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, alignment with divinity signifies something very serious about the person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is they consider themselves to be accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.11,0:06:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.23,0:06:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So the thing that worries me about an atheist is I know he doesn't consider himself accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.11,0:06:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He can say anything he wants and get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.61,0:06:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So you hope that in a gentlemanly way they'll be ethical.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.67,0:06:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you don't believe in God, the next best thing is ethics.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.13,0:06:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ethics, however, depends on perception and reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.58,0:06:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And perception, as we know, is the quickest way to hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.12,0:06:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, trust again, perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.92,0:06:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The other signal of a good, reliable person is a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.12,0:06:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Never trust a person who doesn't have a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.94,0:07:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because a sense of humor signifies the ability to comprehend context as well as content.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.14,0:07:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Humor is contrasting content with context.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.00,0:07:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's where the humor comes forth, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.54,0:07:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what's said, but then the context tells you what it really means.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.34,0:07:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So humor is very useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.92,0:07:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.48,0:07:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has to do, then, with acknowledging disparities.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.23,0:07:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,By humor, you can take two things that seem to spirit and acknowledge the reality of both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.10,0:07:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is also quite modest in a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.12,0:07:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Humor is modest in that it acknowledges there's more than one way to look at a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.29,0:07:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You may not agree with other people's perceptions, but at least you're acknowledging them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.67,0:07:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have an extra bulb, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.70,0:08:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to drive into town and get a bulb?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.30,0:08:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.34,0:08:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, while we're waiting, anybody got any questions?
