Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.42,0:13:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So because it's nonlinear,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.13,0:13:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so the difficulty people have in understanding the work
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.63,0:13:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is they confuse the linear and the nonlinear,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.75,0:13:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll try and get that cleared up today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.72,0:13:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the calibrated levels of consciousness, then, have become relatively well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.02,0:13:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There are study groups all around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.30,0:13:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The books are translated into all the world's languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.86,0:13:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The technique we demonstrate is actually used by various governments, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.30,0:13:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the map of consciousness goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.16,0:14:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from one possibility up to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.31,0:14:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you can see, I think everybody here is rather familiar with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.33,0:14:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It also covers the view of yourself, the view of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.81,0:14:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the emotional states of reason and love that we'll be talking about today,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.34,0:14:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,accompanied by understanding leading to these various states.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.22,0:14:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Above 200 is positive, and below 200 is negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.72,0:14:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So hating and scorning and killing, et cetera, are below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.92,0:14:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And Bin Laden is about 20 or 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.32,0:14:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.42,0:14:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He's someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.30,0:14:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so anyway, we're all familiar with the scale of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.04,0:14:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got any question about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.54,0:14:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got any question about the scale of consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.82,0:14:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.10,0:15:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make your own scale of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.38,0:15:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,from one to 100, or one to a million.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.76,0:15:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And on your scale, then, you have to define at what level
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.64,0:15:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,discerns truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.34,0:15:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so can you see that little dot back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.22,0:15:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.16,0:15:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.06,0:15:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, unfortunately, or fortunately, depending on how you look at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.10,0:15:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for mankind, you see that 85% of the world is below consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.20,0:15:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Level 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.51,0:15:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the implications, the inference, the meaning of that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.77,0:15:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,explains to you why it is very often a difficult world to live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.79,0:15:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because 85% of the people will steal you blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.34,0:15:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, many people will feel it's their duty to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.64,0:16:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you left it out, he deserves it, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.83,0:16:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So 85% of the world is below.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.41,0:16:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Level 200, which explains the nature of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.27,0:16:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fact that man has been at war 93% of recorded time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.36,0:16:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So war, you might say, is his natural state 93% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.78,0:16:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And in today's world, there's only probably five or six wars going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.64,0:16:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rather quiet time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.65,0:16:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.65,0:16:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So here, above 200, there's only 15%.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.17,0:16:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet that 15%, because they have so much power,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.21,0:16:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalance the negativity of the 85% that calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.20,0:16:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, an audience like this, which is way above 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.24,0:16:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is right at this very moment counterbalancing a huge block of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.02,0:17:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This audience sitting here now is counterbalancing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.38,0:17:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,many millions of people that are below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.35,0:17:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.05,0:17:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.73,0:17:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The evolution of consciousness over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.49,0:17:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.13,0:17:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.09,0:17:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We mentioned Henry Stepp.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.31,0:17:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,His new book is out, Mindful Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.87,0:17:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And it explains the theoretical physics behind what we have just demonstrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.89,0:17:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That this process here, if something has reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.62,0:17:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that collapses the wave function.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.88,0:17:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,From the potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.62,0:17:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,From the potential to the actual.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.16,0:17:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way you can collapse the wave function is it has to exist in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.16,0:17:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So if what I hold in mind is real, then it collapses the wave function
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.52,0:17:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the arm indicates truth versus falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.00,0:17:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.74,0:18:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the next slide is, because we're talking about reason today,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.22,0:18:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I always put the great books of the Western world, because they have such a decisive,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.67,0:18:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, part in history, becoming famous, uh, and of course this, this, these are the greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.68,0:18:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,minds that have, have, have been, uh, uh, on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.52,0:18:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest minds, Copernicus, uh, and, and we noticed that the only thing out of step
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.28,0:18:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with all these people you see are in the 400s is Karl Marx at 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.72,0:18:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world were put together, I guess, by Mortimer Adler.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.40,0:18:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, because of his importance, Karl Marx and Engels were put in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.33,0:18:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The, the difficulty is that Marx has gotten de-Marxed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.13,0:18:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not called Karl Marx anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.01,0:19:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, he, he's called something else which they've removed the name Marx.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.00,0:19:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And it now, the same thinkingness at, at below 200, yeah, emerges in our society as relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.52,0:19:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism is Marxism without the word Marx.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.52,0:19:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the result of a deliberate move, uh, to remove any political objection to the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.07,0:19:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,name Marx.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.07,0:19:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So they removed Marx and, uh, the same dialectic, uh, continues in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.73,0:19:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And people say, why, what is far, why does far left calibrate so low?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.99,0:19:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's nothing but Marx, the dialectical materialism of Karl Marx at 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.63,0:19:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Engels was only 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.07,0:19:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.69,0:19:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.95,0:19:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So that explains, uh, the difficulty of the modern world, uh, in, uh, you know, at least
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.75,0:19:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.75,0:19:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go on to the next, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.16,0:20:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, one of the most important implications of level of consciousness is its influence
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.30,0:20:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on brain function.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.16,0:20:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Below level 200, uh, the brain operates, uh, in an animal way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.90,0:20:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The left brain is dominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.28,0:20:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, fight or flight and, uh, release of adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.51,0:20:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, that part of the brain is interested in winning and in gain and getting the better
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.69,0:20:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.18,0:20:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Above level 200, so below 200, you have left brain dominance, uh, the mind is focused on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.92,0:20:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,linear content.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.90,0:20:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't really grasp context.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.72,0:20:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it wrong to monitor communications between Americans and, uh, the other side of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.18,0:20:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.18,0:20:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.40,0:20:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you can argue it either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.76,0:20:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends, uh, on context, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.14,0:20:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're not at war, then it's an invasion of privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.80,0:21:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's, if we are at war, then it's the obligation of the government to protect its citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.96,0:21:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's all imagined matter of context.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.13,0:21:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So below 200, people don't get context.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.95,0:21:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What goes in times of war does not go in times of peace, vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.65,0:21:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if this person has a certain disease, you don't allow him to travel, uh, and infect
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.19,0:21:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,others infect others you see is that a civil rights violation we don't allow him on the plane
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.58,0:21:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,if he's got an incurable form of very active tuberculosis no we don't love it leave him on
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.98,0:21:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the plane why because of the context all right so the right brain then works in a different way
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.43,0:21:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it releases endorphins and a different sort of emotions to people say what can i do to advance
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.73,0:21:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,my own spiritual development and i always say be as loving as possible as you can be and consider
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.57,0:22:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it of uh of all of all of existence and all of life to be kind and considerate also means not
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.98,0:22:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,only to god and your fellow man but also to yourself so when people attack themselves with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.49,0:22:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt they're violating that principle you can correct yourself without attacking yourself with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.30,0:22:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt you don't really have to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.66,0:22:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,hate yourself oh i hate myself or something or other you don't have to hate yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.14,0:22:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so out of benevolence so this benevolence should be extended to all living things all living
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.10,0:22:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,creatures you see the little beetle with his legs flying in the wind and you you just put
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.74,0:22:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,him over on his feet so he can walk away again that same benevolence you forget to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.44,0:22:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,afford your own self what you would do for the black beetle please do that for yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.68,0:22:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as well include yourself as deserving of compassion and consideration and lovingness yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.60,0:23:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,all right so the difficulty of these two civilizations they're really two different
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.72,0:23:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,civilizations have been getting along is for one thing they use a different size of the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.36,0:23:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so how are you going to get uh one side of the brain synchronized with the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.90,0:23:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of the brain and that's some of what we're going to be talking about today yes okay then let's go
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.10,0:23:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,next one. This has to do with the rate of happiness. People say that, you know, happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.08,0:23:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to things that are out there, or it's society's fault, or people are being deprived
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.92,0:23:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of happiness. I've been rich and I've been poor, and frankly, I didn't notice it had any impact at
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.94,0:23:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,all on happiness. It sure had an impact on what you wear. I was so poor, people used to laugh at
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.87,0:24:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,my clothes. And I really saw it after residency at Mount Sinai Hospital in New York. The best
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.04,0:24:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,analysts and everybody was on the staff. And one day the chief secretary called me, and she said
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.14,0:24:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to me, you can't come here dressed like that. You've got to get better clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.68,0:24:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no money, so where am I going to get better clothes with no money? All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.50,0:24:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of happiness has to do with the level of consciousness, has to do with the level of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.16,0:24:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. And the higher the level of consciousness, the higher the level of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.26,0:24:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see as consciousness, once it goes over level 200, the percent of happiness below
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.12,0:24:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,200, hardly anybody's happy. Hardly anybody's happy. Hardly anybody's happy. Hardly anybody's
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.75,0:24:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,happy. And at 200, suddenly it jumped from 22 to 55%. And as consciousness level goes up, so in a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.87,0:25:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,group like this, what did I say, 89? All right. 89% of everybody sitting here should be happy at
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.30,0:25:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,least. If somebody's unhappy, let's cure that person instantly. If somebody's unhappy out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.64,0:25:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,please raise your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.06,0:25:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there an unhappy person? Unhappy, unhappy. Unhappy it can be. Nobody's miserable today.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.00,0:25:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God, how can I? I've got to import somebody miserable to sit in the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.42,0:25:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, they'll think we're faking it. It couldn't be that everybody in this room is happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.58,0:25:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'd say everybody in this room is relatively happy. Happiness is relative, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.42,0:25:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, okay, what's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.04,0:26:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that say? Perception versus essence? Uh, that's too complicated. Let's move to the next
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.95,0:26:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,one. I don't want to bust my brain this morning. Perception versus essence. I thought it was a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.92,0:26:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,picture. Let's move to the next one. All right, we're going to be talking about reason and faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.38,0:26:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason and faith. And probably one of the best exhibits of reason are the great scientists. The
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.28,0:26:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,scientists are all in the mid-400s, and they exhibit the great benefit of thinking this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.84,0:26:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And reason goes up to the highest level of about 499. 499 is Sigmund Freud, Albert Einstein,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.30,0:26:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton, and of course they have changed all of our lives forever. So the 400s are
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.28,0:27:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely powerful, and if it wasn't for the 400s, most of us wouldn't be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.83,0:27:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because out of the 400s came antibiotics, and the cures of many diseases, pasteurizing milk,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.06,0:27:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,etc. All the things that are responsible for our being alive have come out of the 400s. So logic
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.18,0:27:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and reason are extremely powerful. So the 400s are very powerful. It's a very powerful level.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.64,0:27:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of the people in this room will be in the high 400s, or in the middle of the 500s,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.77,0:27:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of the 500s. Okay, so let's move on. So we owe a great deal to science.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.54,0:27:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,God versus science, of course, is very common in today's world. The big argument between
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.94,0:27:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,them. And we'll get back to, here's St. Thomas Aquinas there, 570. Yes, that's who I was
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.94,0:27:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,holding in mind. Okay, so we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.53,0:28:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in every audience, there's a diehard that doesn't want to give up his allegiance to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.79,0:28:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,perception. This is confrontational. What a thing looks like is not necessarily what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.89,0:28:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is, you know? And that explains politics, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.11,0:28:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What a thing looks like, perception, is not the same as essence. And the most important thing that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.03,0:28:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,we really learn about is that we're not the same as the essence. And we're not the same as the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.83,0:28:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,essence. And we're not the same as the essence. And we're not the same as the essence. And we're not
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.85,0:28:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of the work that we've done on consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.49,0:28:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is how to discern essence from appearance, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.51,0:28:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next one.
